 &quot;The Seventh Hammer&quot; one of the very few I could pronouce. So I chose that one.<br><br>When it came time to choose a character, I started with wizard because I remembered wizards were cool in other video games I had played. I remember entering the world for the first time and thinking how cool it was to see another person walking down the street from me. I remember thinking, &quot;Wow, that's a real person.&quot; lol<br><br>I fooled around with the keys and eventually pressed &quot;A&quot;. Since I had targeted myself, the battle music started playing, the text box asked me to stop attacking myself, and I started getting stressed out. I didn't want to kill myself, after all.<br><br>Eventually, I found myself in Greater Faydark and looked for something to beat up. I found a bat (or it found me). Due to my newbieness, dial-up lag, and me not on auto-attack, I soon died. That's wasn't so fun.<br><br>So I played around with other characters. I started a human warrior in Freeport. I wait on the docks for the boat to show up. It did after a long time, and I zoned into the ocean. Zoning for me took five minutes, haha.<br><br>After a few more characters, I went back to the wizard. I read up on a few things and went out to fight bats again. The second time around, I won! Encouraged, I felt invincible until an unexpected encounter with an orc pawn. I learned quickly about running to the guards.<br><br>A half hour later, I got level two. I was so happy. &quot;A level a day!&quot; I thought with a smile. &quot;This game is easy!&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uarinnelessedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ArinnElessedil</A> at: 6/20/02 11:05:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uthuuglyfe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thuug Lyfe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle> 1    Poster<BR><TABLE WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=7 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPA