=1> I started in November of '99, right after I started my freshman year of college.<br><br>Well, my first day of EQ was kind of spent watching my neighbor in the dorms playing his DE SK in Nektulos (on Xegony). He'd skip class to play EQ, and I'd spend all my time between classes watching him play. We had another friend who played a DE Necro (also a dorm neighbor). Of course I wanted to play with them, so I researched what I wanted to be. I had to be an evil healer of some sort, but I didn't want to be a DE because I spent too much time watching my SK friend struggling with encumbrance, and while watching him, I had seen an ogre kill a mummy in like 2 seconds. Looking up the differences between troll and ogre, I went with troll because of the natural regen and the goofy green look.<br><br>So then I finally got a copy of EQ, rolled my shaman (and of course forgot to max my wis at creation), and started playing. By the time I levelled up to like 6 or 7, my dorm neighbors stopped playing but of course by then I was hooked. I spent the next few weeks levelling up (solo. innothule is almost always deserted) on frogloks and young kobolds and orcs before finally being brave enough to venture into South Ro. Of course S Ro was also usually deserted. I did get a group a few times, killing dervs and undead. It was there that I learned about mobs invulnerable to non-magic weapons when my group was wiped out by a ghoul. I was fortunate enough to get a Midnight Mallet a short while later from someone trying to get an Ivandyr's Hoop.<br><br>So I continued levelling (on what I later realized was woefully inadequate equipment), eventually joined a guild (Blood of the Fold) with a friend I had made back in the swamp, and made the switch to Seventh Hammer during the split when I was around level 35.<br> <p><hr align=left width=40% size=3><table><tr><td><img src="http://chip-web.com/~ludwigp/eq/sigpic_09mini.jpg" width=60 height=60></td><td>[60 Oracle] Zugugg Kindso