de sure to stay away from them this time. So, I run all the way out near the fire out there (where those 2 NPCs usually sit), got lost, and eventually ran into...dun, dun, dun! a bat. I attacked it (bare fisted, I thought I had lost my sword), and beat it. But barely! I quickly found my way back to the fire, rested to full health, and went on the hunt again. It was still night time, so I got lost again. I then ran into a decaying skeleton, which I decided to attack. Unfortunately for me, it had another skeleton friend nearby, and it quickly came over to come and beat me up. After dying a second time, I lost interest in the game, and quit. But that wasn't the last time I'd be playing EQ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/ualeguzzler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aleguzzler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table style=filter:glow(color=Blue strength=3><font color=White face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Dorf Extraordinare</font></table> </span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/17/02 3:39:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=205.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Your First Day Of Playing Everquest (Share Your Stories!</span><hr size=1> Rorek was origionally a Paladin, got him to lvl 9, realized Pally's am teh suk. And deleted him restarted with same name only as a Warrior, been playing Rorek non stop ever sinse. <br><br><br><br> <p><center><table style=filter:glow(color=Blue strength=7><font color=White face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3166>Rorek Valdahaz</a></font></table></center><center><table style=filter:glow(c