.<br>It took him three months to talk me into playing, something about getting online with a bunch of other people and having no idea what the hell I was doing made me nervous.<br>Finally Seacanyon got me to make a character, a green eyed Erudite wizard named Kalaluna. I was hooked but I didn't have my own computer much less my own account. I spent hours playing Kala after my best friend had gone to bed. Finally one day I was able to buy a computer and get my own account.<br>I don't know why but for some reason I decided I wanted to be a dark elf, and purple-eyed necromancer appealed to me in some twisted way.<br>So I made Viliu (a computer picked name btw). I stood in Neriak Commons for some time before meeting Cyvarth, a good friend now that was kind enough to show me where the guild was then came to my rescue and later helped me get out of Neriak into the Nektulos and to the newbie log.<br>Seacanyon, trilled not only because I had gotten my own account but because he was finally going to get his computer back, ran over and gave me a few raw silk things he was able to tailor himself.<br>On the first day of life, after things settled down a little bit I met another person that has since become the person Viliu calls her sister, Ivei.<br>I remember how amazed we both were that by just sitting at the newbie log people would look at our equipment then hand us stuff without us even asking. And how awesome it was when we grouped with a high level 20 cleric to kill halflings silly enough to be camped in our forest.<br>My first day was also when I met Rinna Lightshadow, repeatedly and I learned that she has a very rude way of welcoming dark elves. (I swear I'm bringing her down one day). And it was when I also learned how the Paladin guards in North Freeport feel about DE necromancers. I have no idea, other than shear noob dumb luck, how I got from the Neriak entrance in Nektulos to Rinna Lightshadow's hut without dying (I think it was four times because I was trying to get my body back).<br><br><br> <p><B>Viliu Ironscale</B><BR>Inky, Inny luvin' Heretic of 54 winters<BR>Proud member of Steel Thunder - Seventh Hammer<BR><BR>"No I can't give you crack but I can make you dead."<BR><BR><B>Viliea Sombradelaluna</B><BR>Priestess of Innoruuk of 36 winters<BR>Proud member of Steel Thunder<BR><BR>"I'm out of mana but by all means, pull the swardwurm. Someone got bandaids?"<BR><BR><B>Nuthin</B><BR>Attemping to pickpockets for 15 season.<BR>Proud member of Steel Thunder<BR><BR>"That's not a trap, it's just Bristlebane's way of showing you that he loves ya."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uchubbylumpkinsanklesbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chubbylumpkins Anklesbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style=width: 100%; font-family: Arial Black; color: white; Filter: Shadow(Color=#808080, Direction=225)>Super n0me!</span></span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/17/02 6:29:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=205.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Your First Day Of Playing Everquest (Share Your Stories!</span><hr size=1> My first character was a troll...I spent ages running around grobb looking for a way out, until I found out that if I jumped in the lava I would appear outside of town!<br><br>There was a mystique about EQ then for me, I really, really wish it still had that mystique. I was in awe of the whole thing...turned out to be nothing like I had hoped...oh well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>I guess what you expected EQ to be could be a whole other thread. <p><font size=