orch and made it back, almost died training the gnolls to the zone.   It was there that I met my first longtime friend, a shaman named Grumblefish.  Not sure if he still plays, but he has a bard named &quot;Churro&quot; for a while.<br><br>Then I eventually made it into an elite ledge group. I can't remember everone in that group, except there was Muppo, (level 7 Gnome magician at the time) and Mikah (a level 11 Ranger, and he had banded mail). I had a Morning star... yes the plain 8 damage 40 delay non magic kind you buy in a store for 17 plat.  There was also another shaman in the group but I can't remember her name. I DO know that she convinced me to run to freeport for my night vision spell, and got me into an orc 1 group in EC a couple days later.<br><br>I remember muppo and I dinged on the same kill, he got level 8, and I got level 9. I was amazed by his pet... it rooted stuff and looked really cool, and I remember that I had read that shamans got a pet at some really high level, and wondering if I'd ever get that high.<br><br>The next couple months I ambled through the levels, I kept muppo on my friends list (he still plays, his monk is named Xukanis) and he very quickly rose through the levels.  I eventually ventured to faydwer and checked out crushbone, because I hated oasis with a passion.<br><br>It was there in crushbone that I got invited to join a tower group, and partnered with Relan (who was also level 17 at the time, and had full banded) and I met Wory, who was Clad in full bronze armor with a Langseax of the wolves.  Wory reccomended me and I later joined the guild &lt;Blademasters&gt; where I met then Chubby, Tavist, Danicah, Erathko, Smirnoff (aka Kjia), and a number of other great people.  Also Xanais joined the blades a couple days after me.<br><br>Then I headed to unrest, and fought there a bit until my friend Grumblefish (Now playing Churro) tells me to come to the overthere, he's found a great spot to fight, without too many people, yet easy to get a group.  So I make the trek and finally get to kunark. Within 30 seconds of zoning in, (it was raining and I couldn't see anything) I was killed by dark elf guards at the fort, and my body is in the water.... The GM at the time was kind enough to ressurect me, had never met a guide before... but a wizard with a sword sure looked funny.<br><br>From there I hunted at the mud pit a while, and headed to the dreaded zone that is Lake of Ill omen. I hated this zone (there were surprisingly few lamers then) so I left and headed back to unrest, where I managed to ding 24, and finally become a real shaman (Cannibalize and Regen, gotta love it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br><br>Oh yeah, I remember raiding Dalnir with the blades, we had a kick ass group that I was too low (level 24) to get experience in, because chubby was like 44 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  still, it rocked <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><table align="center" border="5" style="border-collapse: collapse; font-family: Arial; color: #8888FF; bordercolor="#9999FF" bordercolorlight="#5555FF" bordercolordark="#000088"><tr><td align="center" bgcolor="#000000" WIDTH="234"><FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" SIZE=+0><IMG SRC="http://www.grizlorspics.iwarp.com/tunaresuxsmall.jpg"><BR><I>Deny your Maker</i></font></td><td bgcolor="#000000" align="center"><B><FONT COLOR="#5555FF">My Toons:</b><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45358" target="_blank"><b> </font><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Grizlor</a></b></font> Shaman<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48124" target="_blank"><B><FONT COLOR="#CDDFF">Bigbrawler</a></b></font> Monk<BR><a 