acers. Yay. But he got wasted a lot so I quit him.<br><br>Around this time my friend of such wise suggestions told me to come to 7th Hammer (because he got someone's account password and stole his uber warrior gear - crafted and a charred guardian breastplate). He played that character and I started another, better, druid, by the name of Sinx (math = suk), and played him a while. Got him to 16 and had a little nest egg from uber bind moniez and SOW donations, so I made an SK, called him Eitsekur. Yay. Bronze helm from a passerby, some soft wicker, and later an almost full suit of Blackened Alloy armor from Ravenclaw (woot for ranger). And that was really my first day of EQ, because up until then all my days were sucky in comparison. <p><table width="294" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#000000" border="1" bordercolor="#000000" align="center">  <tr>     <td width="137" height="212"><img src="http://pages.sbcglobal.net/tele/_images/Eitsig001.jpg" width="137" height="296"></td>    <td width="147" valign="top" height="212">       <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89448"><font color="#FF3300"><b><br>        <font color="#FF9900">Eitsekur</font></b></font></a><br>        Erudite Shadowknight<br>        Officer </font></p>      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile?num=200637"><font color="#FF9900">Miktoffel</font></a>         <br>        Dark Elf Wizard<br>        Member</font></p>      <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1" color="#FFFFFF"><a href="http://mythrilmoon.tripod.com"><font color="#FF9900"><span class="unnamed1">Mythrilmoon         Mystics </span></font></a><br>        <br>        <br>        I</font><font size="1" color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">         am the way into the city of woe<br>        I am the way 